verbose_text: Interestingly, exposure of acute promyelocytic leukemia NB4 cells to oridonin resulted in a significant increase in ROS generation while the ROS scavenger, N-acetylcysteine (NAC), completely protected NB4 cells from oridonin induced apoptosis.
evidence: ROS scavenger, N-acetylcysteine (NAC), completely protected NB4 cells from oridonin-induced apoptosis
